# TypeScript Types Standards

## Organization

- `types/api.ts` — shared base types (`BaseEntity`, `ApiResponse<T>`)
- `types/[feature].ts` — feature-specific interfaces
- `types/index.ts` — centralized re-exports

## Base Types (`types/api.ts`)

```typescript
export interface BaseEntity {
  id: string;
  userId: string;
  createdAt: number;
}

export interface ApiResponse<T> {
  success: boolean;
  data?: T;
  error?: string;
}
```

## Feature Types Pattern

```typescript
// types/feature.ts
import { BaseEntity } from './api';

export interface Feature extends BaseEntity {
  title: string;
  description: string;
}

export interface FeatureInput {
  title: string;
  description: string;
}

export interface FeatureFormData {
  title: string;
  description: string;
}
```

- `Feature` — full entity returned by the API (extends `BaseEntity`)
- `FeatureInput` — shape sent to the API on create/update
- `FeatureFormData` — local form state (may differ from `FeatureInput`)

## API Response Usage

Always type responses with `ApiResponse<T>`:

✅ **GOOD:**

```typescript
const result: ApiResponse<Feature[]> = await response.json();
if (!result.success) throw new Error(result.error);
return result.data ?? [];
```

❌ **BAD — never define custom response shapes inline:**

```typescript
const data = await response.json(); // untyped
interface MyResponse { success: boolean; data: Feature[]; } // duplicate
```

## Centralized Exports

```typescript
// types/index.ts
export type { ApiResponse, BaseEntity } from './api';
export type { Feature, FeatureInput, FeatureFormData } from './feature';
```
